Package fel.cvut.pjv

Class GameController

  • java.lang.Object
    • fel.cvut.pjv.GameController
  • public class GameController
extends java.lang.Object
    Handles all requests to modify model: Handles creation and movement of bullets. Handles movement of vehicles. Handles collisions. Handles explosions. Is thread safe.

      • removeAi

        public void removeAi​(EnemyTankDriver driver)
        Removes driver reference from AiList. Also removes its vehicle from gameboard and adds its last position to be updated in next frame.
        Parameters:
        driver - driver to be removed.

      • isAiListEmpty

        public boolean isAiListEmpty()

      • startGame

        public void startGame​(java.lang.String playerName)
        Starts game. Calls GameView to render GUI, initializes and starts BulletDriver, GameLoop. Starts AIs. Can be called only AFTER initializing GameBoard.

      • moveVehicle

        public void moveVehicle​(Vehicle vehicle,
                        int[] requestedDirection)
        Moves vehicle by 1 tile in requested direction. Handles entity activation when they get driven on. If requested direction does not match vehicle direction vehicle is rotated without moving.
        Parameters:
        vehicle - vehicle to be moved - must not be null.
        requestedDirection - direction which the vehicle shall be moved/rotated.

      • moveBullet

        public void moveBullet​(Bullet bullet)
        Moves bullet by 1 tile. Handles bullet running out of range and collisions. Bullets that move out of bounds are removed. Handles notifying BulletDriver upon bullet explosion, so they can be removed.
        Parameters:
        bullet - - bullet to be moved in its facing direction.

      • explodeTiles

        public void explodeTiles​(int rowPos,
                         int colPos,
                         int radius,
                         int damage,
                         Vehicle author)
        Sets ExplosionTile in specified radius around explosion position. All explosions have an author because of keeping score. Explosions that would be out of bounds are not created. Handles hitting entities with said explosion upon creation. Handles removing entities if they are destroyed by the explosion.
        Parameters:
        rowPos - center position of explosion
        colPos - center position of explosion
        author - creator of explosion - if entity is hit he will get score for it.
        radius - how many tiles around requested position are also exploded. 0 explodes only requested position, 1 explodes 3x3 area with requested position in the middle.

      • shoot

        public void shoot​(Vehicle vehicle)
        Creates new Bullet instance and adds it to BulletDriver. Facing direction of bullet is based on current facing direction of vehicle. Handles attempts to create bullet out of bound or inside another entity.
        Parameters:
        vehicle - author of bullet.

      • savePlayerStats

        public void savePlayerStats​(int[] playerStats)
        Saves player stats to corresponding playerfile.
        Parameters:
        playerStats - stats to save for player in format {health, armor, damage}.

      • saveScore

        public void saveScore()
        Increments corresponding playerscore in score file.
